{"id":19121,"title":"[Invasive candidiasis in newborns: diagnosis, treatment and prophylaxis].","abstract":"Invasive fungal infections have become an increasingly common problem in neonatal intensive care units (NICU). Invasive candidiasis (IC) is associated with substantial morbidity and mortality rates, especially in pre-term infants. The aim of this review is to suggest actions in monitoring, prevention, treatment and follow up of IC in the newborn infant. ","date":"2014-04-17","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24740778","annotations":[{"name":"Death","weight":0.803478,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death"},{"name":"Prophylaxis","weight":0.794623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prophylaxis"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.787846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Neonatal intensive care unit","weight":0.787178,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neonatal_intensive_care_unit"},{"name":"Mortality rate","weight":0.781524,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mortality_rate"},{"name":"Intensive care unit","weight":0.756514,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive_care_unit"},{"name":"Morbidity","weight":0.752758,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morbidity"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.751095,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.738937,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Infant","weight":0.709797,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infant"},{"name":"Candidiasis","weight":0.709591,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Candidiasis"},{"name":"Intensive-care medicine","weight":0.706275,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intensive-care_medicine"},{"name":"Fungus","weight":0.669581,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fungus"},{"n